# Scenario: DNS RESOLUTION FAILURE — Quectel EC25-G. Modem is fully attached,
# IP-layer is healthy (pings to 8.8.8.8 succeed cleanly), but pings to
# hostnames fail with QPING error 565 ("DNS lookup failed"). This is a
# brand-new fault class my analyzer doesn't have a rule for — it should
# show up as a gap because the heuristic "data path is healthy" returns
# True even though name resolution is broken.
# Expected SE diagnosis: DNS misconfiguration. The device is using
# carrier-assigned DNS but those servers may be blocked, or the device
# firmware has hardcoded/stale DNS settings.
# Customer guidance:
#   1. Confirm IP-layer works:  AT+QPING=1,"8.8.8.8"   (already in the log)
#   2. Check DNS:  AT+QIDNSCFG=1     (Quectel-specific DNS config readout)
#   3. Override with public DNS: AT+QIDNSCFG=1,"8.8.8.8","1.1.1.1"
#   4. Have the application code retry DNS on failure rather than caching the result.

